{"TopicId":124417,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.8.0-1.12.5] AtmosphereAutopilot 1.6.1","CreatedByName":"Boris-Barboris","CreatedById":133181,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-11-04T09:42:36Z","PageNum":38,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Boris-Barboris","CreatedById":133181,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-23T12:02:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224238216\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677120776\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176387\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Theesteban 667\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Theesteban 667 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you try to restart AA, even the complete game.\u003Cbr\u003E\nCould I explain what the flight model is?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s under the submenu that is shown when you hover the \u0022AA\u0022 button on the sidebar (that icon tray where fuel panel and other mod buttons are placed).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Theesteban 667","CreatedById":176387,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-23T20:56:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224238601\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677153746\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133181\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Boris-Barboris\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Boris-Barboris said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003EEst\u00E1 debajo del submen\u00FA que se muestra cuando pasa el bot\u00F3n \u0022AA\u0022 en la barra lateral ( que la bandeja del icono donde se colocan el panel de combustible y otros botones de modificaci\u00F3n ). \u003C/font\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t really find it, could you post a picture of what it looks like?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Boris-Barboris","CreatedById":133181,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-24T06:40:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224239252\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677185774\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176387\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Theesteban 667\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Theesteban 667 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t really find it, could you post a picture of what it looks like?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022i44TzeX.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002243.37\u0022 height=\u002285\u0022 width=\u0022196\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/i44TzeX.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Theesteban 667","CreatedById":176387,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-24T08:27:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224239652\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677220822\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133181\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Boris-Barboris\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Boris-Barboris said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/i44TzeX.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022i44TzeX.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002243.37\u0022 height=\u002285\u0022 width=\u0022196\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/i44TzeX.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022JkPdd4g.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002285.25\u0022 height=\u0022960\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/JkPdd4g.png\u0022\u003EHolla here is the departure of the flight model, thanks for your patience\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Boris-Barboris","CreatedById":133181,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-25T13:56:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224239682\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677227230\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176387\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Theesteban 667\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/24/2023 at 11:27 AM, Theesteban 667 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHollahere is the departure of the flight model, thanks for your patience\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWas AA broken when you took this screenshot? Seems healthy to me...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DianonForce","CreatedById":121367,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-05T13:14:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi,\u003Cbr\u003E\ni hope you can help me.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI build a starter plane with a tuboshaft engine. It flys okish with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E, but as soon as i activate Autopilot, it rolls clockwise with insane rate and never stops.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nwith autopilot on\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022autopilotOn.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002293.17\u0022 height=\u0022533\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022http://forcestar.synology-ds.de/autopilotOn.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwith autopilot on\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022autopilotOff.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002297.00\u0022 height=\u0022554\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022http://forcestar.synology-ds.de/autopilotOff.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Boris-Barboris","CreatedById":133181,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-05T13:23:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224252434\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678022053\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022121367\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DianonForce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, DianonForce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut as soon as i activate Autopilot, it rolls clockwise with insane rate and never stops.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat is the name of the part that is used as propeller blade?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGenerally, yeah, I didn\u0027t test it on DLC props, and the math assumes fixed-wing plane with no moving parts (\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a workaround coded, but it obviously fails in your case.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-05T13:24:54Z\u0022 title=\u002203/05/2023 01:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 5, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Boris-Barboris\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DianonForce","CreatedById":121367,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-05T13:35:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis one\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022prop.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002269.61\u0022 height=\u0022433\u0022 width=\u0022622\u0022 src=\u0022http://forcestar.synology-ds.de/prop.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Boris-Barboris","CreatedById":133181,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-05T13:40:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224252445\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678023354\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022121367\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DianonForce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, DianonForce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis one\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, sorry. I opened the code, and it looks like AA will not work with propellers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hippodingo","CreatedById":205497,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-11T11:04:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour mod is really nice and I\u0027ve been using it for a long time. Is there a simple way to use it in IVA (with RPM notably)? I tried with kOS and Baker script but I can\u0027t make it work properly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBasically, I would like to use autopilot like IRL, with buttons in the cockpit to change target heading, altitude, speed and vertical speed. I am opened to learn how to make buttons interact with AA script (like for example if I press one button in IVA, heading will get \u002B1).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for your help!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Boris-Barboris","CreatedById":133181,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-11T13:39:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224256930\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678532687\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022205497\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hippodingo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Hippodingo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a simple way to use it in IVA (with RPM notably)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! I\u0027m afraid, no, there isn\u0027t.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UndeadFirefly","CreatedById":228104,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-21T08:07:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi. I\u0027m having issues with oscillation when FBW is turned on. If I turn it on before takeoff the plane immediately pitches down to the ground right after takeoff. If I turn it on mid flight the plane pitches up and down constantly and if the speed is high enough it gets ripped apart. I\u0027m using the default profile and I also have \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E and Procedural Wings installed. What can I do to mitigate this issue?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tg626","CreatedById":112361,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-22T04:47:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDunno about the pitch dn on the rw, but oscillation (hunting) can be the result of excessive authority. Might be something to look at.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"rogerwang86","CreatedById":189926,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-14T16:54:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003EAny possible let\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(255,255,255);font-size:17px;\u0022\u003EAtmosphereAutopilot controll more than one rudder on one part?\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022EsLskvg.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://imgur.com/EsLskvg.gif\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Boris-Barboris","CreatedById":133181,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-14T20:28:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224283304\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221684083258\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022189926\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022rogerwang86\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, rogerwang86 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003EAny possible let\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(255,255,255);font-size:17px;\u0022\u003EAtmosphereAutopilot controll more than one rudder on one part?\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you mean split rudder than no. If not, you\u0027ll need to elaborate.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"rogerwang86","CreatedById":189926,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-15T08:48:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224283362\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221684096127\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133181\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Boris-Barboris\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Boris-Barboris said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you mean split rudder than no.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, is there any way to make split rudder work? Like add a plugin? I can write C# so if there is any chance to make it work, I willing to try.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Boris-Barboris","CreatedById":133181,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-15T12:03:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224283478\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221684140483\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022189926\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022rogerwang86\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, rogerwang86 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, is there any way to make split rudder work? Like add a plugin? I can write C# so if there is any chance to make it work, I willing to try.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry, don\u0027t see a simple solution on design level, coding is a lesser problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"rogerwang86","CreatedById":189926,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-15T19:38:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224283518\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221684152209\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133181\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Boris-Barboris\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Boris-Barboris said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry, don\u0027t see a simple solution on design level, coding is a lesser problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthank you, will looking\u00A0 another way to fix it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-12T15:12:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m trying to use AA to automate the ascent to cruise level.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo do such, on the \u003Cstrong\u003ECruise Flight Controller\u003C/strong\u003E I set the desired Airspeed on the \u003Cstrong\u003ESpeed control\u003C/strong\u003E, and then on \u003Cstrong\u003EVertical motion\u003C/strong\u003E I set a \u003Cstrong\u003EVertical speed\u003C/strong\u003E that keeps the throttle control at 100%, but without dropping the current Airspeed below the desired one. Rinse, repeat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCumbersome, because I would like to have the thing doing it automatically to me, so I can focus on other things while the craft is climbing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a way to automate this using AA? I.e., once the aircraft reaches the target Airspeed with the throttle at 100%, the \u003Cstrong\u003EVertical speed\u003C/strong\u003E is gradually increased instead of the Throttle being decreased? At the same time, if the current Airspeed drops below the target, the \u003Cstrong\u003EVertical speed\u003C/strong\u003E is gradually decreased until the speed matches again the target.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would make my cruising missions\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Eway\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0more comfortable!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf there\u0027s no currently available option to do such, I will gladly implement it myself (and do a pull request into the mainstream) if someone could guide me in the process!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Boris-Barboris","CreatedById":133181,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-12T15:25:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224292504\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221686582726\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187168\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lisias\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, Lisias said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m trying to use AA to automate the ascent to cruise level.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo do such, on the \u003Cstrong\u003ECruise Flight Controller\u003C/strong\u003E I set the desired Airspeed on the \u003Cstrong\u003ESpeed control\u003C/strong\u003E, and then on \u003Cstrong\u003EVertical motion\u003C/strong\u003E I set a \u003Cstrong\u003EVertical speed\u003C/strong\u003E that keeps the throttle control at 100%, but without dropping the current Airspeed below the desired one. Rinse, repeat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCumbersome, because I would like to have the thing doing it automatically to me, so I can focus on other things while the craft is climbing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a way to automate this using AA? I.e., once the aircraft reaches the target Airspeed with the throttle at 100%, the \u003Cstrong\u003EVertical speed\u003C/strong\u003E is gradually increased instead of the Throttle being decreased? At the same time, if the current Airspeed drops below the target, the \u003Cstrong\u003EVertical speed\u003C/strong\u003E is gradually decreased until the speed matches again the target.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would make my cruising missions\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Eway\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0more comfortable!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf there\u0027s no currently available option to do such, I will gladly implement it myself (and do a pull request into the mainstream) if someone could guide me in the process!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry FLC vertical motion mode, should suit you better on climb.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHistory:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022149977\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4541985369\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/124417-180-1123-atmosphereautopilot-160/?do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2452657\u0026amp;embedComment=2452657\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-12T19:51:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224292508\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221686583511\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133181\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Boris-Barboris\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Boris-Barboris said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry FLC vertical motion mode, should suit you better on climb.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh, so this is the meaning on the \u0022Pseudo FLC\u0022 button! Thank you very much!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn time, while toying with the thing, I ended up mistyping a value (ended up typing a \u0022,\u0022 instead of \u0022.\u0022 as my keyboard is PT-BR) and the damned thing gone 737 MAX (and since I use the GPWS add\u0027on, I crashed hearing that terrifying \u0022PULL UP\u0022 alarm! My spine is still frozen...).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, I think I had solved this problem on the pull request\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Boris-Barboris/AtmosphereAutopilot/pull/39\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Boris-Barboris/AtmosphereAutopilot/pull/39\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease review it and advise any change you want me to do!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheers!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Boris-Barboris","CreatedById":133181,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-09T20:03:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224292565\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221686599489\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187168\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lisias\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/12/2023 at 10:51 PM, Lisias said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh, so this is the meaning on the \u0022Pseudo FLC\u0022 button! Thank you very much!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn time, while toying with the thing, I ended up mistyping a value (ended up typing a \u0022,\u0022 instead of \u0022.\u0022 as my keyboard is PT-BR) and the damned thing gone 737 MAX (and since I use the GPWS add\u0027on, I crashed hearing that terrifying \u0022PULL UP\u0022 alarm! My spine is still frozen...).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, I think I had solved this problem on the pull request\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Boris-Barboris/AtmosphereAutopilot/pull/39\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Boris-Barboris/AtmosphereAutopilot/pull/39\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease review it and advise any change you want me to do!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheers!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRelease 1.6.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Boris-Barboris/AtmosphereAutopilot/releases/tag/v1.6.1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Boris-Barboris/AtmosphereAutopilot/releases/tag/v1.6.1\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdd FPA (flight-path angle) vertical speed mode for Cruise Flight controller.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nBetter handling of input errors in GUI text fields.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks to \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/187168-lisias/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022187168\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/187168-lisias/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Lisias\u003C/a\u003E and @T2Fat2Fly for their contributions!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HafCoJoe","CreatedById":80363,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-09T20:13:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224301046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221688933008\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133181\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Boris-Barboris\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, Boris-Barboris said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRelease 1.6.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Boris-Barboris/AtmosphereAutopilot/releases/tag/v1.6.1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Boris-Barboris/AtmosphereAutopilot/releases/tag/v1.6.1\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdd FPA (flight-path angle) vertical speed mode for Cruise Flight controller.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nBetter handling of input errors in GUI text fields.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks to \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/187168-lisias/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022187168\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/187168-lisias/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Lisias\u003C/a\u003E and @T2Fat2Fly for their contributions!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWoah, that feature sounds incredibly useful for SSTOs to be able to set a specific angle to hold! I.E. 10 degree incline, hold until orbit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-07-09T20:23:50Z\u0022 title=\u002207/09/2023 08:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 9, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by HafCoJoe\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Test-Account-KSP","CreatedById":229862,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-10T08:39:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis looks like an important step toward autoland!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:happy:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/happy.png\u0022 title=\u0022:happy:\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:happy:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/happy.png\u0022 title=\u0022:happy:\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:happy:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/happy.png\u0022 title=\u0022:happy:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf there was also a mode that doesn\u0027t simply flies to a waypoint, but intercepts a radial to waypoint that is set on the runway, AA would already be able to fly an approach.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpacedInvader","CreatedById":106018,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-24T04:34:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222405765\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022124417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221455303710\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133181\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Boris-Barboris\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/12/2016 at 12:01 PM, Boris-Barboris said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill do in next release, if i will find ergonomic way to.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWas this option ever added, and if so, how can I access it? Have been looking through the buttons and config file, but can\u0027t seem to find any way to switch from the main toolbar to Blizzy\u0027s where I keep all of my \u0022mission critical\u0022 buttons.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}